Difference Between List and NumPy Array
Python List	NumPy Array
Slower	Faster
Can store different data types	Usually stores same data type
More memory	Less memory
Limited mathematical operations	Supports vectorized operations

Example

import numpy as np

l = [1,2,3]

a = np.array([1,2,3])

print(l * 2)

Output

[1,2,3,1,2,3]

But

print(a * 2)

Output

[2 4 6]

NumPy performs element-wise multiplication.

Shapes of the Arrays
import numpy as np

arr1 = np.array([1,2,3,4,5])
print(arr1.shape)
# (5,)

arr2 = np.array([[1,2,3],[4,5,6]])
print(arr2.shape)
# (2,3)

ten = np.array([
    [[1,2],[3,4]],
    [[4,3],[2,1]]
])

print(ten.shape)
# (2,2,2)
